                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.014,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has our opinion this morning in case 13-1175, City of Los Angeles v. Patel."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.014,
                        "stop": 209.328,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15131,
                            "name": "Sonia Sotomayor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sonia_sotomayor",
                            "last_name": "Sotomayor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2776,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1249707600,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": null,
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2776"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32685,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 50379,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sonia_sotomayor_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 2293,
                            "identifier": "sonia_sotomayor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.014,
                                "stop": 13.782,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case comes to us from the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.782,
                                "stop": 23.891,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Los Angeles Municipal Code requires hotel operators to maintain records containing certain information regarding their guests."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.891,
                                "stop": 34.2,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It also compels hotels to make these records available to any officer of the Los Angeles Police Department for inspection on demand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.2,
                                "stop": 55.051,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The questions presented are whether facial challenges to statutes authorizing warrantless searches can be brought under the Fourth Amendment, and if so, whether the provision of the LA Code that requires hotel operators to turn over their guests\u0027 registries to the police is facially invalid."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.051,
                                "stop": 63.619,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We first clarify that facial challenges under the Fourth Amendment are not categorically barred or especially disfavored."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.619,
                                "stop": 70.142,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A facial challenge is an attack on a statute itself as opposed to a particular application."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.142,
                                "stop": 78.443,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court has never held that such claims cannot be brought under any otherwise enforceable provision of the Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.443,
                                "stop": 81.09,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Fourth Amendment is no exception."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.09,
                                "stop": 89.226,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Indeed on numerous occasions this Court has declared statutes facially invalid under the Fourth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.226,
                                "stop": 105.342,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Turning to the merits of respondent\u0027s claim we begin with the well-established rule that searches conducted without prior approval by a judge are per se unreasonable subject to only a few well-defined exceptions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.342,
                                "stop": 115.154,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "One exception is for administrative searches, that is, searches intended to serve an aim other than a general interest in crime control."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.154,
                                "stop": 128.195,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We assume that the searches at issue here serve such a purpose ensuring that hotels are complying with the city\u0027s record-keeping requirements, but that is not the end of our analysis."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.195,
                                "stop": 147.584,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We have held that for an administrative search to be reasonable under the Fourth Amendment the subject of the search must be given an opportunity to obtain pre-compliance review in front of a neutral decision-maker before facing penalties for refusing to comply with the search."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.584,
                                "stop": 153.482,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We see no reason why this minimal requirement should not apply here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.482,
                                "stop": 170.412,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Absent an opportunity for pre-compliance review Los Angeles law creates an intolerable risk that the searches that it authorizes will exceed statutory limits or be used as a pretext to harass hotel operators and their guests."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.412,
                                "stop": 181.889,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Regardless of how frequently a hotel is searched, the operator can only refuse to comply with an officer\u0027s demand to turn over the registry at his or her own peril."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.889,
                                "stop": 195.286,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we affirm the Ninth Circuit\u0027s holding that the provision of the LA Code that compels hotel operators to turn over their guests\u0027 registries to police on demand is facially unconstitutional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.286,
                                "stop": 201.959,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice and Justice Thomas join."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.959,
                                "stop": 209.328,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Thomas joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
